HP has launched its Omen X compact gaming PC on its online store. The Omen X Compact Desktop is a convertible desktop PC and VR backpack, allowing gamers to play VR titles without being tethered to a desk. A docking station allows users to charge the backpackâ€™s battery and use the device as a conventional gaming PC. The slim chassis houses an overclockable Intel Core i7 processor and Nvidia GeForce GTX 1080 graphics card, offering enough power for VR and 4K gaming. The device is available for $2,499.